               <p>Q. You produce the affidavit sworn to, in Joseph the defendant, and Nathan the plaintiff - A. This is it; it was sworn before me; he was sworn by the Pentateuch.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you know whether he is a jew, or not - A. I do not. I swear a jew by the Old Testament.</p>
               <p>Mr. Gurney. If a man of the name of Price, Jones, or Smith, you would give him the New Testament - A. Yes, and if a man of the name of 
               <persName id="t18130714-130-person1238">Nathan</persName>
             I should give him the Old.</p>
               <p>COURT. How are the words in the affidavit - A. That he was then, and there duly sworn by the Holy Gospels of God.</p>
